<subSubSection id="8C8E6575FF516AEEFA63948A16E6B876" pageId="170" pageNumber="932" type="conservation">
<paragraph id="C42B36FEFF516AEEFA63948A16E6B876" blockId="170.[1435,2644,289,880]" pageId="170" pageNumber="932">
<emphasis id="F6E0EAECFF516AEEFA63948A18FCB9C6" bold="true" box="[1439,1788,723,756]" pageId="170" pageNumber="932">Status and Conservation.</emphasis>
Classified as Endangered on The IUCN Red List. All Findley’s 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFF516AEEFA63955A1BF9B82E" authority="Kaup, 1829" box="[1439,1529,771,796]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Myotis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="170" pageNumber="932" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Myotis</taxonomicName>
occur in fewer than five locations. Threats include urban development, livestock, wood harvest, and introduction of non-native species.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
